In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reflects on the significance of Thanksgiving and expresses gratitude for various blessings and individuals. He references historical moments such as George Washington declaring a day of Thanksgiving for his troops at Valley Forge and Abraham Lincoln proclaiming the holiday during the Civil War. President Biden acknowledges the challenging year and expresses gratitude for those who have supported the nation, including farm workers, frontline workers, educators, parents, healthcare professionals, researchers, scientists, and troops. He also shares personal traditions and highlights the importance of unity and goodwill. Finally, President Biden proclaims Thursday, November 25, 2021, as a National Day of Thanksgiving and encourages the people of the United States to come together and express gratitude for the support they have received.